One critical correction to your current execution instruction set



Your “Non-negotiable rule #1” says LangGraph must not mutate filesystem directly. But the orchestrator must create the run directory (or call a dedicated tool to do it). Pick one and codify it:


Preferred: run_dir_init_cli tool (single responsibility)
LangGraph calls it; you keep “no direct FS mutation” pure.

Acceptable: orchestrator creates only .acms_runs/{run_id} skeleton and nothing else; all other writes happen via tools.


If you do not explicitly decide this, you’ll reintroduce implied behavior.



